text.tspan: Change in CO₂ emissions and GDP
Consumption-based emissions are national emissions that have been adjusted for trade. This measures fossil
fuel and industry emissions. Land-use change is not included.
Data source: World Bank (2023); Global Carbon Budget (2024)
Note: Gross Domestic Product (GDP) figures are adjusted for inflation.
